We at Ill Gotten Games are big fans of the [Vintage RPG Podcast](https://www.stitcher.com/podcast/unwinnable-3/the-vintage-rpg-podcast), and after designing a model for Hambone [the hammer-wielding ranger, Johan](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3483772)), I made one for Stu as well. This is Greel, an opportunistic (but deep down, gold-hearted) ex-mercenary company leader/current warlock with a magic ring that can turn him into a tree at the first sight of danger. The model prints without support.

If you haven't checked it out, Hambone and Stu (Horvath, from [unwinnable.com](https://unwinnable.com/)) do a weekly podcast where they discuss tabletop games, and do deep dives into RPGs old and new. This all branches off of Stu's excellent [Instagram feed](https://www.instagram.com/vintagerpg/?hl=en), which is always an insightful read if you're into the history and current state of tabletop roleplaying games. We're proud to be [supporting them on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/vintagerpg/overview), and you should really check out what they're doing/throw them some bones if you like it as much as we do.

Starting today, we're launching "Monster Mondays," a regular feature where we upload a new monster miniature design to our online [storefront](http://www.illgottengames.net/products/?category=Miniatures), with our [Patreon supporters](https://www.patreon.com/illgottengames) getting free access. Though not technically a monster, she'll be the narrator of our growing monster compendium, and you can consider this "entry zero." The Knight, like all the miniatures we're designing for this game, prints without the need of support material. We printed ours without a raft and at a .1 layer height with 10% infill.
